The announcement of the likely discovery of Higgs boson caused a great shock last summer, and rightly.
It is believed, in fact, that this boson is participate of the responsible mechanism of the mass of all that exists in the universe, nothing more and nothing less.
And what is more, it is the particle whose existence predicts the standard model: our better or "less bad" explanation of the nature and behavior of matter, which has not yet been observed empirically.
